(26527, 400, 2598, 'description', '<p style="text-align: justify" class="MsoNormal"><strong>Position Summary:</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: justify" class="MsoNormal"><strong>&nbsp;</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal"><span style="color: #333333">The\r\nEHS Data Backup Administrator is a critical role within our Client''s IT\r\nOperations Group. Under the oversight of the solutions architecture manager ,\r\nthe Backup Engineer will ensure that the day-to-day backup routines for the\r\nuser data on 300+ file, print, application and database servers is backed up\r\ndaily, stored securely and recoverable utilizing backup Exec, </span><span>NetBackup Tivoli, and CommVault.&nbsp; The Backup\r\nEngineer should have a minimum of 5 years&rsquo; experience managing backups on an\r\nenterprise scale.&nbsp; The Backup Engineer should have a working knowledge of\r\ncurrent data disaster recovery practices.&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal"><span style="color: red">&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal"><span style="color: #333333">The\r\nBackup Administrator will: engineer, support, administer and maintain all\r\nstorage related technology. This includes all storage devices and applicable\r\nsoftware (i.e. Tape, Disk, SAN, Backup Systems, etc.) for the entire\r\nSecretariat. The backup engineer will be responsible for effective\r\nprovisioning, installation/configuration, operation, and maintenance of systems\r\nhardware and software as it relates to the enterprise backup environment. The\r\nbackup engineer will perform daily system monitoring, verifying the integrity\r\nand availability of all backed up data. Daily reporting as it relates to\r\nbackups is expected. <strong><u>Statewide (MA) travel is required (and reimbursed).</u></strong><br />\r\n<br />\r\n<strong>Major Responsibilities</strong>: </span><span style="color: #212121"></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="margin-left: 51pt" class="MsoNormal"><span style="color: #333333">&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;\r\n</span><span style="color: #333333">Configuration\r\nand implementation of backup software</span><span style="color: #212121"></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="margin-left: 51pt" class="MsoNormal"><span style="color: #333333">&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;\r\n</span><span style="color: #333333">Performance and\r\nmaintenance of backup servers</span><span style="color: #212121"></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="margin-left: 51pt" class="MsoNormal"><span style="color: #333333">&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;\r\n</span><span style="color: #333333">Backup capacity\r\nplanning</span><span style="color: #212121"></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="margin-left: 51pt" class="MsoNormal"><span style="color: #333333">&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;\r\n</span><span style="color: #333333">Trend Analysis</span><span style="color: #212121"></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="margin-left: 51pt" class="MsoNormal"><span style="color: #333333">&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;\r\n</span><span style="color: #333333">Regularly\r\nscheduled audits</span><span style="color: #212121"></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="margin-left: 51pt" class="MsoNormal"><span style="color: #333333">&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;\r\n</span><span style="color: #333333">Offsite and\r\nonsite storage of media</span><span style="color: #212121"></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="margin-left: 51pt" class="MsoNormal"><span style="color: #333333">&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;\r\n</span><span style="color: #333333">Tape management</span><span style="color: #212121"></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="margin-left: 51pt" class="MsoNormal"><span style="color: #333333">&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;\r\n</span><span style="color: #333333">Data Retention\r\nCompliancy</span><span style="color: #212121"></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="margin-left: 51pt" class="MsoNormal"><span style="color: #333333">&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;\r\n</span><span style="color: #333333">Ensures total\r\nstored data availability</span><span style="color: #212121"></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal"><span style="color: #333333">Backup Engineer leads and\r\ncoordinates the engineering phases of storage solutions delivery including\r\nplanning, design, build, testing, ordering and transition to operational\r\nsupport.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nUndertakes complex projects requiring specialized knowledge of storage\r\ntechnologies, services and applications.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nBackup Engineer provides analysis, design and direction regarding performance\r\nmanagement and capacity planning services with regard to backups.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nAdditionally, the Backup Engineer will work closely with the Systems\r\nEngineering and Operations Management in planning and executing upgrades\r\nutilizing new technologies while maintaining existing backup systems and\r\nservices.</span><span style="color: #212121"></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal">&nbsp;</p>', '<p style="text-align: justify" class="MsoNormal"><strong>Position Summary:</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: justify" class="MsoNormal"><strong>&nbsp;</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal"><span style="color: #333333">The\r\nEHS Data Backup Administrator is a critical role within our Client''s IT\r\nOperations Group. Under the oversight of the solutions architecture manager ,\r\nthe Backup Engineer will ensure that the day-to-day backup routines for the\r\nuser data on 300+ file, print, application and database servers is backed up\r\ndaily, stored securely and recoverable utilizing backup Exec, </span><span>NetBackup Tivoli, and CommVault.&nbsp; The Backup\r\nEngineer should have a minimum of 5 years&rsquo; experience managing backups on an\r\nenterprise scale.&nbsp; The Backup Engineer should have a working knowledge of\r\ncurrent data disaster recovery practices.&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal"><span style="color: red">&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal"><span style="color: #333333">The\r\nBackup Administrator will: engineer, support, administer and maintain all\r\nstorage related technology. This includes all storage devices and applicable\r\nsoftware (i.e. Tape, Disk, SAN, Backup Systems, etc.) for the entire\r\nSecretariat. The backup engineer will be responsible for effective\r\nprovisioning, installation/configuration, operation, and maintenance of systems\r\nhardware and software as it relates to the enterprise backup environment. The\r\nbackup engineer will perform daily system monitoring, verifying the integrity\r\nand availability of all backed up data. Daily reporting as it relates to\r\nbackups is expected. <strong><u>Statewide (MA) travel is required (and reimbursed).</u></strong><br />\r\n<br />\r\n<strong>Major Responsibilities</strong>: </span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="margin-left: 51pt" class="MsoNormal"><span style="color: #333333">&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;\r\n</span><span style="color: #333333">Configuration\r\nand implementation of backup software</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="margin-left: 51pt" class="MsoNormal"><span style="color: #333333">&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;\r\n</span><span style="color: #333333">Performance and\r\nmaintenance of backup servers</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="margin-left: 51pt" class="MsoNormal"><span style="color: #333333">&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;\r\n</span><span style="color: #333333">Backup capacity\r\nplanning</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="margin-left: 51pt" class="MsoNormal"><span style="color: #333333">&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;\r\n</span><span style="color: #333333">Trend Analysis</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="margin-left: 51pt" class="MsoNormal"><span style="color: #333333">&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;\r\n</span><span style="color: #333333">Regularly\r\nscheduled audits</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="margin-left: 51pt" class="MsoNormal"><span style="color: #333333">&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;\r\n</span><span style="color: #333333">Offsite and\r\nonsite storage of media</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="margin-left: 51pt" class="MsoNormal"><span style="color: #333333">&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;\r\n</span><span style="color: #333333">Tape management</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="margin-left: 51pt" class="MsoNormal"><span style="color: #333333">&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;\r\n</span><span style="color: #333333">Data Retention\r\nCompliancy</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="margin-left: 51pt" class="MsoNormal"><span style="color: #333333">&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;\r\n</span><span style="color: #333333">Ensures total\r\nstored data availability</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal"><span style="color: #333333">Backup Engineer leads and\r\ncoordinates the engineering phases of storage solutions delivery including\r\nplanning, design, build, testing, ordering and transition to operational\r\nsupport.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nUndertakes complex projects requiring specialized knowledge of storage\r\ntechnologies, services and applications.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nBackup Engineer provides analysis, design and direction regarding performance\r\nmanagement and capacity planning services with regard to backups.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nAdditionally, the Backup Engineer will work closely with the Systems\r\nEngineering and Operations Management in planning and executing upgrades\r\nutilizing new technologies while maintaining existing backup systems and\r\nservices.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal">&nbsp;</p>', '(USER) changed field(s): title, description.', '2017-04-10 08:49:17', 1265, 1),
