(121237492, 400, 2653, 'description', '<h2 style="padding: 0px; margin-right: 0px; margin-left: 0px; font-family: Lato, sans-serif; -webkit-font-smoothing: antialiased; line-height: 27px; border: 0px; font-variant-ligatures: no-common-ligatures; font-variant-numeric: inherit; font-stretch: inherit; font-size: 20px; vertical-align: baseline; color: #0d0d0d; font-feature-settings: ''liga'' 0, ''clig'' 0; box-sizing: border-box; margin-top: 0px !important; margin-bottom: 12px !important" class="noMargTop margBotSm strong">job DescriptionGENERAL FUNCTION: Makes decisions on complex architecture issues. Coordinates with users to determine requirements and design systems to fit their needs. Ensures system improvements are successfully implemented and monitored to increase efficiency. Establishes and communicates common goals for team members. Acts as resource for less experienced staff.<br /><span style="color: #555555; font-size: 15px; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-weight: 500">The position is on the Technical/Professional ladder at level 4 in the Technology Architecture discipline.&nbsp;</span><br /><span style="color: #555555; font-size: 15px; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-weight: 500">Responsible and accountable for risk by openly exchanging ideas and opinions, elevating concerns, and personally following policies and procedures as defined. Accountable for always doing the right thing for customers and colleagues, and ensures that actions and behaviors drive a positive customer experience. While operating within the Bank#s risk appetite, achieves results by consistently identifying, assessing, managing, monitoring, and reporting risks of all types.</span><br /><span style="color: #555555; font-size: 15px; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-weight: 500">DUTIES &amp; RESPONSIBILITIES:&nbsp;</span><br /><span style="color: #555555; font-size: 15px; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-weight: 500">1. Plays a key role as the technical architect for projects. Responsible for detailed technical architecture and design for complex projects.&nbsp;</span><br /><span style="color: #555555; font-size: 15px; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-weight: 500">2. Functions as a technical expert for a major business line in the design, development, modification and debugging of programs, job streams, network diagrams, hardware plans and related activities. Ensures that projects follow the prescribed development life cycle and meet quality standards.</span><br /><span style="color: #555555; font-size: 15px; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-weight: 500">3. Acts as a technical expert addressing problems relating to systems integration, compatibility, and multiple platform integration.&nbsp;</span><br /><span style="color: #555555; font-size: 15px; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-weight: 500">4. Keeps current with trends and technological innovations in the banking and IT industry, and makes appropriate development recommendations.&nbsp;</span><br /><span style="color: #555555; font-size: 15px; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-weight: 500">5. Interacts and consults with appropriate business analysts to understand application requirements and defines architectural components to meet those requirements.&nbsp;</span><br /><span style="color: #555555; font-size: 15px; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-weight: 500">6. Develops architectural plans supportive of the business objectives of the application area.&nbsp;</span><br /><span style="color: #555555; font-size: 15px; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-weight: 500">7. Documents architecture appropriately and consistently within the defined architectural process.&nbsp;</span><br /><span style="color: #555555; font-size: 15px; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-weight: 500">8. Other duties as required.&nbsp;</span><br /><span style="color: #555555; font-size: 15px; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-weight: 500">SUPERVISORY RESPONSIBILITIES:&nbsp;</span><br /><span style="color: #555555; font-size: 15px; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-weight: 500">None</span><br /><span style="color: #555555; font-size: 15px; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-weight: 500">Minimum Skills &amp; ExperienceMINIMUM KNOWLEDGE, SKILLS AND ABILITIES REQUIRED:</span><br /><span style="color: #555555; font-size: 15px; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-weight: 500">Undergraduate degree or Masters with 5 or more years of experience. In-depth knowledge of the technology base of all Group applications.</span></h2>', '<h2 style="padding: 0px; margin-right: 0px; margin-left: 0px; font-family: Lato, sans-serif; -webkit-font-smoothing: antialiased; line-height: 27px; border: 0px; font-variant-ligatures: no-common-ligatures; font-variant-numeric: inherit; font-stretch: inherit; font-size: 20px; vertical-align: baseline; color: #0d0d0d; font-feature-settings: ''liga'' 0, ''clig'' 0; box-sizing: border-box; margin-top: 0px !important; margin-bottom: 12px !important" class="noMargTop margBotSm strong"><blockquote style="margin: 10px 0px 10px 10px; padding-left: 10px; border-left: 2px solid #cccccc; color: #999999; font-family: Tahoma, Geneva, sans-serif; font-size: 12.09px; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-weight: normal"><div style="margin: 0px; padding: 0px"><font face="arial" size="2"><div id="SafeStyles1496330108" style="margin: 0px; padding: 0px"><div class="WordSection1" style="margin: 0px; padding: 0px; page: WordSection1"><p style="margin: 0px; padding: 0px; font-size: 10pt; word-wrap: break-word" class="wordsection1"><strong><span style="font-size: 10pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif">Job Description:</span></strong></p><p style="margin: 0px; padding: 0px; font-size: 10pt; word-wrap: break-word" class="wordsection1"><span style="font-size: 10pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif">&nbsp;</span></p><p style="margin: 0px; padding: 0px; font-size: 10pt; word-wrap: break-word" class="wordsection1"><span style="font-size: 10pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif">We are in search of an Enterprise Architect with at least 6+ years of IT experience. An ideal candidate will have a strong development background and at least a year or two of recent architecture experience. This role will not involve any development. This is a strategy/ future planning focused position.</span></p><p style="margin: 0px; padding: 0px; font-size: 10pt; word-wrap: break-word" class="wordsection1"><span style="font-size: 10pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif">&nbsp;</span></p><p style="margin: 0px; padding: 0px; font-size: 10pt; word-wrap: break-word" class="wordsection1"><span style="text-decoration-line: underline"><span style="font-size: 10pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif">Enterprise Solution Architect job details:</span></span></p><p style="margin: 0px; padding: 0px; font-size: 10pt; word-wrap: break-word">&nbsp;</p><p style="margin: 0px 0in 6pt 0.5in; padding: 0px; font-size: 12pt; font-family: ''Times New Roman'', serif; text-indent: -0.25in" class="wordsection1"><span style="font-size: 10pt; font-family: Symbol">&middot;<span style="font-stretch: normal; font-size: 7pt; line-height: normal">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</span></span><span style="font-size: 10pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif">This role requires knowledge of high-level system design and integration, along with strong leadership characteristics.&nbsp;</span></p><p style="margin: 0px 0in 6pt 0.5in; padding: 0px; font-size: 12pt; font-family: ''Times New Roman'', serif; text-indent: -0.25in" class="wordsection1"><span style="font-size: 10pt; font-family: Symbol">&middot;<span style="font-stretch: normal; font-size: 7pt; line-height: normal">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</span></span><strong><span style="font-size: 10pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif">Need to have a solid understanding of architectural best practices, good problem solving abilities, general integration design expertise, and a good understanding of technology</span></strong><span style="font-size: 10pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif">&nbsp;is helpful, etc. (Knowledge of MQ, Web Services, Java, etc. is helpful, but not mandatory)</span></p><p style="margin: 0px 0in 6pt 0.5in; padding: 0px; font-size: 12pt; font-family: ''Times New Roman'', serif; text-indent: -0.25in" class="wordsection1"><span style="font-size: 10pt; font-family: Symbol">&middot;<span style="font-stretch: normal; font-size: 7pt; line-height: normal">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</span></span><span style="font-size: 10pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif">The primary responsibility is to collaborate with technical leads across the Fifth Third organization to come up with a technical approach (and document it) that complies with enterprise standards while at the same time meeting project timelines.</span></p><p style="margin: 0px 0in 6pt 0.5in; padding: 0px; font-size: 12pt; font-family: ''Times New Roman'', serif; text-indent: -0.25in" class="wordsection1"><span style="font-size: 10pt; font-family: Symbol">&middot;<span style="font-stretch: normal; font-size: 7pt; line-height: normal">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</span></span><span style="font-size: 10pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif">They would be&nbsp;<strong>working on Strategic projects</strong>&nbsp;that would start at the Concept Definition Stage, then take the projects from Concepts all the way to the Development Teams.&nbsp; These projects could range across various departments from either Enterprise, Commercial, Payments, to Retail &amp; Consumer IT, etc.&nbsp;</span></p><p style="margin: 0px 0in 6pt 0.5in; padding: 0px; font-size: 12pt; font-family: ''Times New Roman'', serif; text-indent: -0.25in" class="wordsection1"><span style="font-size: 10pt; font-family: Symbol">&middot;<span style="font-stretch: normal; font-size: 7pt; line-height: normal">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</span></span><strong><span style="font-size: 10pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif">Experience building future blueprints and roadmaps</span></strong></p><p style="margin: 0px 0in 6pt 0.5in; padding: 0px; font-size: 12pt; font-family: ''Times New Roman'', serif; text-indent: -0.25in" class="wordsection1"><span style="font-size: 10pt; font-family: Symbol">&middot;<span style="font-stretch: normal; font-size: 7pt; line-height: normal">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</span></span><span style="font-size: 10pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif">Create architecture documentation, using appropriate standards</span></p><p style="margin: 0px; padding: 0px; font-size: 10pt; word-wrap: break-word" class="wordsection1"><span style="font-size: 10pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif">&nbsp;</span></p><p style="margin: 0px; padding: 0px; font-size: 10pt; word-wrap: break-word" class="wordsection1"><span style="font-size: 10pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif">*This is a true architect position. This resource will&nbsp;<span style="text-decoration-line: underline">not</span>&nbsp;actively be doing day to day development in this position.</span></p></div></div></font></div></blockquote></h2>', '(USER) changed field(s): description.', '2017-06-05 10:55:59', 1253, 1),
